'''''Grand National''''' is a 1985 [[video game]] for the [[ZX Spectrum]] from [[United Kingdom|British]] publisher [[Elite Systems]]. It is based on the horse race of the [[Grand National|same name]]. The goal is to win a race with your chosen horse at [[Aintree Racecourse]] while also having a [[Gambling|bet]] on the outcome. An [[Amiga]] port was published in 1989.

==Gameplay==
[[Image:Grand National Spectrum.png|thumb|right|Spectrum screenshot]]
Players must adjust there speed and avoid hedges and other competitors.<ref>{{cite book |last1=Wilkins |first1=Chris |title=The Little Book of Sinclair ZX Spectrum Games |date=2016 |publisher=Fusion Retro Books |page=14 |language=English}}</ref> Rapidly alternating between two keys makes the horse run. Another key jumps over fences.

